# Tracing Musical Lineage Through Databases
M1 IPP S2 — Paulin Rosset

## Prerequisites
- PostgreSQL 18/15
- Python 3.10+
- pip install psycopg2 streamlit plotly pandas

## Step 1 — Download MusicBrainz data
Go to: https://ftp.musicbrainz.org/pub/musicbrainz/data/fullexport/20260418-002325/
Download: mbdump.tar.bz2 and mbdump-derived.tar.bz2
Extract both into a folder called: musicbrainz/

## Step 2 — Create the database
Open psql and run:
  CREATE DATABASE musicbrainz ENCODING 'UTF8';

## Step 3 — Apply the schema in your terminal (in this order)
psql -U postgres -d musicbrainz -f Extensions.sql
psql -U postgres -d musicbrainz -f CreateTypes.sql
psql -U postgres -d musicbrainz -f CreateTables.sql
psql -U postgres -d musicbrainz -f CreateFunctions.sql
psql -U postgres -d musicbrainz -f CreatePrimaryKeys.sql
psql -U postgres -d musicbrainz -f CreateIndexes.sql
psql -U postgres -d musicbrainz -f CreateFKConstraints.sql
psql -U postgres -d musicbrainz -f CreateConstraints.sql

## Step 4 — Import the data
Edit import.py to set data_dir to your mbdump folder path and put your postre password
python import.py

## Step 5 — Run the dashboard
python -m streamlit run music_dashboard.py
